Here is the complete HTML code that retains the image input selector, allowing users both to select an image and input an integer from 0 to 63 to dictate which sides of the hexagon should have circles drawn based on the binary representation of the number. 

When the user selects an image, it will be used for drawing the circles on the hexagon sides whenever a binary '1' is present. 

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>Hexagon Circle Selector with Image</title>
<style>
body {
    font-family: sans-serif;
